46 TinyPtrVector llvm::FindDbgDeclareUses(Value *V) { 0
47 // This function is hot. Check whether the value has any metadata to avoid a ----
48 // DenseMap lookup. ----
49 if (!V->isUsedByMetadata()) 0
50 return {}; 0
51 auto *L = LocalAsMetadata::getIfExists(V); 0
52 if (!L) 0
53 return {}; 0
54 auto *MDV = MetadataAsValue::getIfExists(V->getContext(), L); 0
55 if (!MDV) 0
56 return {}; 0
57 ----
58 TinyPtrVector Declares; 0
59 for (User *U : MDV->users()) { 0
60 if (auto *DDI = dyn_cast(U)) 0
61 Declares.push_back(DDI); 0
62 } ----
63 ----
64 return Declares; 0
65 } 0

68 static void findDbgIntrinsics(SmallVectorImpl &Result, Value *V) { 0
69 // This function is hot. Check whether the value has any metadata to avoid a ----
70 // DenseMap lookup. ----
71 if (!V->isUsedByMetadata()) 0
72 return; 0
73 ----
74 LLVMContext &Ctx = V->getContext(); 0
75 // TODO: If this value appears multiple times in a DIArgList, we should still ----
76 // only add the owning DbgValueInst once; use this set to track ArgListUsers. ----
77 // This behaviour can be removed when we can automatically remove duplicates. ----
78 // V will also appear twice in a dbg.assign if its used in the both the value ----
79 // and address components. ----
80 SmallPtrSet EncounteredIntrinsics; 0
81 ----
82 /// Append IntrinsicT users of MetadataAsValue(MD). ----
83 auto AppendUsers = [&Ctx, &EncounteredIntrinsics, &Result](Metadata *MD) { 0
84 if (auto *MDV = MetadataAsValue::getIfExists(Ctx, MD)) { 0
85 for (User *U : MDV->users()) 0
86 if (IntrinsicT *DVI = dyn_cast(U)) 0
87 if (EncounteredIntrinsics.insert(DVI).second) 0
88 Result.push_back(DVI); 0
89 } ----
90 }; ----
91 ----
92 if (auto *L = LocalAsMetadata::getIfExists(V)) { 0
93 AppendUsers(L); 0
94 for (Metadata *AL : L->getAllArgListUsers()) 0
95 AppendUsers(AL); 0
96 } ----
97 } 0

139 void DebugInfoFinder::processModule(const Module &M) { 0
140 for (auto *CU : M.debug_compile_units()) 0
141 processCompileUnit(CU); 0
142 for (auto &F : M.functions()) { 0
143 if (auto *SP = cast_or_null(F.getSubprogram())) 0
144 processSubprogram(SP); 0
145 // There could be subprograms from inlined functions referenced from ----
146 // instructions only. Walk the function to find them. ----
147 for (const BasicBlock &BB : F) 0
148 for (const Instruction &I : BB) 0
149 processInstruction(M, I); 0
150 } ----
151 } 0

153 void DebugInfoFinder::processCompileUnit(DICompileUnit *CU) { 0
154 if (!addCompileUnit(CU)) 0
155 return; 0
156 for (auto *DIG : CU->getGlobalVariables()) { 0
157 if (!addGlobalVariable(DIG)) 0
158 continue; 0
159 auto *GV = DIG->getVariable(); 0
160 processScope(GV->getScope()); 0
161 processType(GV->getType()); 0
162 } ----
163 for (auto *ET : CU->getEnumTypes()) 0
164 processType(ET); 0
165 for (auto *RT : CU->getRetainedTypes()) 0
166 if (auto *T = dyn_cast(RT)) 0
167 processType(T); 0
168 else ----
169 processSubprogram(cast(RT)); 0
170 for (auto *Import : CU->getImportedEntities()) { 0
171 auto *Entity = Import->getEntity(); 0
172 if (auto *T = dyn_cast(Entity)) 0
173 processType(T); 0
174 else if (auto *SP = dyn_cast(Entity)) 0
175 processSubprogram(SP); 0
176 else if (auto *NS = dyn_cast(Entity)) 0
177 processScope(NS->getScope()); 0
178 else if (auto *M = dyn_cast(Entity)) 0
179 processScope(M->getScope()); 0
180 } ----
181 } ----

201 return; 0

212 processType(T); 0

215 } ----
216 return; 0
217 } ----

249 void DebugInfoFinder::processSubprogram(DISubprogram *SP) { 0
250 if (!addSubprogram(SP)) 0
251 return; 0
252 processScope(SP->getScope()); 0
253 // Some of the users, e.g. CloneFunctionInto / CloneModule, need to set up a ----
254 // ValueMap containing identity mappings for all of the DICompileUnit's, not ----
255 // just DISubprogram's, referenced from anywhere within the Function being ----
256 // cloned prior to calling MapMetadata / RemapInstruction to avoid their ----
257 // duplication later as DICompileUnit's are also directly referenced by ----
258 // llvm.dbg.cu list. Thefore we need to collect DICompileUnit's here as well. ----
259 // Also, DICompileUnit's may reference DISubprogram's too and therefore need ----
260 // to be at least looked through. ----
261 processCompileUnit(SP->getUnit()); 0
262 processType(SP->getType()); 0
263 for (auto *Element : SP->getTemplateParams()) { 0
264 if (auto *TType = dyn_cast(Element)) { 0
265 processType(TType->getType()); 0
266 } else if (auto *TVal = dyn_cast(Element)) { 0
267 processType(TVal->getType()); 0
268 } ----
269 } ----
270 } ----

342 MDNode *OrigLoopID, function_ref Updater) { ----
343 assert(OrigLoopID && OrigLoopID->getNumOperands() > 0 && 0

360 // Insert the self-referential LoopID. ----

374 /// Return true if a node is a DILocation or if a DILocation is ----
375 /// indirectly referenced by one of the node's children. ----
376 static bool isDILocationReachable(SmallPtrSetImpl &Visited, 0
377 SmallPtrSetImpl &Reachable, ----
378 Metadata *MD) { ----
379 MDNode *N = dyn_cast_or_null(MD); 0
380 if (!N) 0
381 return false; 0
382 if (isa(N) || Reachable.count(N)) 0
383 return true; 0
384 if (!Visited.insert(N).second) 0
385 return false; 0
386 for (auto &OpIt : N->operands()) { 0
387 Metadata *Op = OpIt.get(); 0
388 if (isDILocationReachable(Visited, Reachable, Op)) { 0
389 // Don't return just yet as we want to visit all MD's children to ----
390 // initialize DILocationReachable in stripDebugLocFromLoopID ----
391 Reachable.insert(N); 0
392 } ----
393 } ----
394 return Reachable.count(N); 0
395 } ----

397 static bool isAllDILocation(SmallPtrSetImpl &Visited, 0
398 SmallPtrSetImpl &AllDILocation, ----
399 const SmallPtrSetImpl &DIReachable, ----
400 Metadata *MD) { ----
401 MDNode *N = dyn_cast_or_null(MD); 0
402 if (!N) 0
403 return false; 0
404 if (isa(N) || AllDILocation.count(N)) 0
405 return true; 0
406 if (!DIReachable.count(N)) 0
407 return false; 0
408 if (!Visited.insert(N).second) 0
409 return false; 0
410 for (auto &OpIt : N->operands()) { 0
411 Metadata *Op = OpIt.get(); 0
412 if (Op == MD) 0
413 continue; 0
414 if (!isAllDILocation(Visited, AllDILocation, DIReachable, Op)) { 0
415 return false; 0
416 } ----
417 } ----
418 AllDILocation.insert(N); 0
419 return true; 0
420 } ----

422 static Metadata * ----
423 stripLoopMDLoc(const SmallPtrSetImpl &AllDILocation, 0
424 const SmallPtrSetImpl &DIReachable, Metadata *MD) { ----
425 if (isa(MD) || AllDILocation.count(MD)) 0
426 return nullptr; 0
427 ----
428 if (!DIReachable.count(MD)) 0
429 return MD; 0
430 ----
431 MDNode *N = dyn_cast_or_null(MD); 0
432 if (!N) 0
433 return MD; 0
434 ----
435 SmallVector Args; 0
436 bool HasSelfRef = false; 0
437 for (unsigned i = 0; i < N->getNumOperands(); ++i) { 0
438 Metadata *A = N->getOperand(i); 0
439 if (!A) { 0
440 Args.push_back(nullptr); 0
441 } else if (A == MD) { 0
442 assert(i == 0 && "expected i==0 for self-reference"); 0
443 HasSelfRef = true; 0
444 Args.push_back(nullptr); 0
445 } else if (Metadata *NewArg = 0
446 stripLoopMDLoc(AllDILocation, DIReachable, A)) { 0
447 Args.push_back(NewArg); 0
448 } ----
449 } ----
450 if (Args.empty() || (HasSelfRef && Args.size() == 1)) 0
451 return nullptr; 0
452 ----
453 MDNode *NewMD = N->isDistinct() ? MDNode::getDistinct(N->getContext(), Args) 0
454 : MDNode::get(N->getContext(), Args); 0
455 if (HasSelfRef) 0
456 NewMD->replaceOperandWith(0, NewMD); 0
457 return NewMD; 0
458 } 0

460 static MDNode *stripDebugLocFromLoopID(MDNode *N) { 0
461 assert(!N->operands().empty() && "Missing self reference?"); 0
462 SmallPtrSet Visited, DILocationReachable, AllDILocation; 0
463 // If we already visited N, there is nothing to do. ----
464 if (!Visited.insert(N).second) 0
465 return N; 0
466 ----
467 // If there is no debug location, we do not have to rewrite this ----
468 // MDNode. This loop also initializes DILocationReachable, later ----
469 // needed by updateLoopMetadataDebugLocationsImpl; the use of ----
470 // count_if avoids an early exit. ----
471 if (!llvm::count_if(llvm::drop_begin(N->operands()), 0
472 [&Visited, &DILocationReachable](const MDOperand &Op) { 0
473 return isDILocationReachable( 0
474 Visited, DILocationReachable, Op.get()); 0
475 })) ----
476 return N; 0
477 ----
478 Visited.clear(); 0
479 // If there is only the debug location without any actual loop metadata, we ----
480 // can remove the metadata. ----
481 if (llvm::all_of(llvm::drop_begin(N->operands()), 0
482 [&Visited, &AllDILocation, 0
483 &DILocationReachable](const MDOperand &Op) { 0
484 return isAllDILocation(Visited, AllDILocation, 0
485 DILocationReachable, Op.get()); 0
486 })) ----
487 return nullptr; 0
488 ----
489 return updateLoopMetadataDebugLocationsImpl( 0
490 N, [&AllDILocation, &DILocationReachable](Metadata *MD) -> Metadata * { 0
491 return stripLoopMDLoc(AllDILocation, DILocationReachable, MD); 0
492 }); 0
493 } 0

561 /// Helper class to downgrade -g metadata to -gline-tables-only metadata. ----
562 class DebugTypeInfoRemoval { ----
563 DenseMap Replacements; ----
564 ----
565 public: ----
566 /// The (void)() type. ----
567 MDNode *EmptySubroutineType; ----
568 ----
569 private: ----
570 /// Remember what linkage name we originally had before stripping. If we end ----
571 /// up making two subprograms identical who originally had different linkage ----
572 /// names, then we need to make one of them distinct, to avoid them getting ----
573 /// uniqued. Maps the new node to the old linkage name. ----
574 DenseMap NewToLinkageName; ----
575 ----
576 // TODO: Remember the distinct subprogram we created for a given linkage name, ----
577 // so that we can continue to unique whenever possible. Map ----
578 // node, old linkage name> to the first (possibly distinct) mdsubprogram ----
579 // created for that combination. This is not strictly needed for correctness, ----
580 // but can cut down on the number of MDNodes and let us diff cleanly with the ----
581 // output of -gline-tables-only. ----
582 ----
583 public: ----
584 DebugTypeInfoRemoval(LLVMContext &C) 0

588 Metadata *map(Metadata *M) { 0

590 return nullptr; 0

592 if (Replacement != Replacements.end()) 0
593 return Replacement->second; 0
594 ----
595 return M; 0
596 } ----
597 MDNode *mapNode(Metadata *N) { return dyn_cast_or_null(map(N)); } 0
598 ----
599 /// Recursively remap N and all its referenced children. Does a DF post-order ----
600 /// traversal, so as to remap bottoms up. ----
601 void traverseAndRemap(MDNode *N) { traverse(N); } 0
602 ----
603 private: ----
604 // Create a new DISubprogram, to replace the one given. ----
605 DISubprogram *getReplacementSubprogram(DISubprogram *MDS) { 0
606 auto *FileAndScope = cast_or_null(map(MDS->getFile())); 0
607 StringRef LinkageName = MDS->getName().empty() ? MDS->getLinkageName() : ""; 0
608 DISubprogram *Declaration = nullptr; 0
609 auto *Type = cast_or_null(map(MDS->getType())); 0
610 DIType *ContainingType = ----
611 cast_or_null(map(MDS->getContainingType())); 0
612 auto *Unit = cast_or_null(map(MDS->getUnit())); 0
613 auto Variables = nullptr; 0
614 auto TemplateParams = nullptr; 0
615 ----
616 // Make a distinct DISubprogram, for situations that warrent it. ----
617 auto distinctMDSubprogram = [&]() { 0
618 return DISubprogram::getDistinct( 0
619 MDS->getContext(), FileAndScope, MDS->getName(), LinkageName, 0
620 FileAndScope, MDS->getLine(), Type, MDS->getScopeLine(), 0
621 ContainingType, MDS->getVirtualIndex(), MDS->getThisAdjustment(), 0
622 MDS->getFlags(), MDS->getSPFlags(), Unit, TemplateParams, Declaration, 0
623 Variables); 0
624 }; 0
625 ----

627 return distinctMDSubprogram(); 0
628 ----
629 auto *NewMDS = DISubprogram::get( 0

631 FileAndScope, MDS->getLine(), Type, MDS->getScopeLine(), ContainingType, ----
632 MDS->getVirtualIndex(), MDS->getThisAdjustment(), MDS->getFlags(), ----
633 MDS->getSPFlags(), Unit, TemplateParams, Declaration, Variables); 0
634 ----
635 StringRef OldLinkageName = MDS->getLinkageName(); 0
636 ----
637 // See if we need to make a distinct one. ----
638 auto OrigLinkage = NewToLinkageName.find(NewMDS); 0
639 if (OrigLinkage != NewToLinkageName.end()) { 0
640 if (OrigLinkage->second == OldLinkageName) 0
641 // We're good. ----
642 return NewMDS; 0
643 ----
644 // Otherwise, need to make a distinct one. ----
645 // TODO: Query the map to see if we already have one. ----
646 return distinctMDSubprogram(); 0
647 } ----
648 ----
649 NewToLinkageName.insert({NewMDS, MDS->getLinkageName()}); 0
650 return NewMDS; 0
651 } ----
652 ----
653 /// Create a new compile unit, to replace the one given ----
654 DICompileUnit *getReplacementCU(DICompileUnit *CU) { 0
655 // Drop skeleton CUs. ----
656 if (CU->getDWOId()) 0
657 return nullptr; 0
658 ----
659 auto *File = cast_or_null(map(CU->getFile())); 0
660 MDTuple *EnumTypes = nullptr; 0
661 MDTuple *RetainedTypes = nullptr; 0
662 MDTuple *GlobalVariables = nullptr; 0
663 MDTuple *ImportedEntities = nullptr; 0
664 return DICompileUnit::getDistinct( 0
665 CU->getContext(), CU->getSourceLanguage(), File, CU->getProducer(), ----
666 CU->isOptimized(), CU->getFlags(), CU->getRuntimeVersion(), 0
667 CU->getSplitDebugFilename(), DICompileUnit::LineTablesOnly, EnumTypes, ----
668 RetainedTypes, GlobalVariables, ImportedEntities, CU->getMacros(), ----
669 CU->getDWOId(), CU->getSplitDebugInlining(), 0
670 CU->getDebugInfoForProfiling(), CU->getNameTableKind(), 0
671 CU->getRangesBaseAddress(), CU->getSysRoot(), CU->getSDK()); 0
672 } ----
673 ----
674 DILocation *getReplacementMDLocation(DILocation *MLD) { 0
675 auto *Scope = map(MLD->getScope()); 0
676 auto *InlinedAt = map(MLD->getInlinedAt()); 0
677 if (MLD->isDistinct()) 0
678 return DILocation::getDistinct(MLD->getContext(), MLD->getLine(), 0
679 MLD->getColumn(), Scope, InlinedAt); 0
680 return DILocation::get(MLD->getContext(), MLD->getLine(), MLD->getColumn(), 0
681 Scope, InlinedAt); 0
682 } ----
683 ----
684 /// Create a new generic MDNode, to replace the one given ----
685 MDNode *getReplacementMDNode(MDNode *N) { 0
686 SmallVector Ops; 0
687 Ops.reserve(N->getNumOperands()); 0
688 for (auto &I : N->operands()) 0
689 if (I) 0
690 Ops.push_back(map(I)); 0
691 auto *Ret = MDNode::get(N->getContext(), Ops); 0
692 return Ret; 0
693 } 0
694 ----
695 /// Attempt to re-map N to a newly created node. ----
696 void remap(MDNode *N) { 0
697 if (Replacements.count(N)) 0
698 return; 0
699 ----
700 auto doRemap = [&](MDNode *N) -> MDNode * { 0
701 if (!N) 0
702 return nullptr; 0
703 if (auto *MDSub = dyn_cast(N)) { 0
704 remap(MDSub->getUnit()); 0
705 return getReplacementSubprogram(MDSub); 0
706 } ----
707 if (isa(N)) 0
708 return EmptySubroutineType; 0
709 if (auto *CU = dyn_cast(N)) 0
710 return getReplacementCU(CU); 0
711 if (isa(N)) 0
712 return N; 0
713 if (auto *MDLB = dyn_cast(N)) 0
714 // Remap to our referenced scope (recursively). ----
715 return mapNode(MDLB->getScope()); 0
716 if (auto *MLD = dyn_cast(N)) 0
717 return getReplacementMDLocation(MLD); 0
718 ----
719 // Otherwise, if we see these, just drop them now. Not strictly necessary, ----
720 // but this speeds things up a little. ----
721 if (isa(N)) 0
722 return nullptr; 0
723 ----
724 return getReplacementMDNode(N); 0
725 }; 0
726 Replacements[N] = doRemap(N); 0
727 } ----
728 ----
729 /// Do the remapping traversal. ----
730 void traverse(MDNode *); ----
731 }; ----
732 ----
733 } // end anonymous namespace ----
734 ----
735 void DebugTypeInfoRemoval::traverse(MDNode *N) { 0
736 if (!N || Replacements.count(N)) 0
737 return; 0
738 ----
739 // To avoid cycles, as well as for efficiency sake, we will sometimes prune ----
740 // parts of the graph. ----
741 auto prune = [](MDNode *Parent, MDNode *Child) { 0
742 if (auto *MDS = dyn_cast(Parent)) 0
743 return Child == MDS->getRetainedNodes().get(); 0
744 return false; 0
745 }; ----
746 ----
747 SmallVector ToVisit; 0
748 DenseSet Opened; 0
749 ----
750 // Visit each node starting at N in post order, and map them. ----
751 ToVisit.push_back(N); 0
752 while (!ToVisit.empty()) { 0
753 auto *N = ToVisit.back(); 0
754 if (!Opened.insert(N).second) { 0
755 // Close it. ----
756 remap(N); 0
757 ToVisit.pop_back(); 0
758 continue; 0
759 } ----
760 for (auto &I : N->operands()) 0
761 if (auto *MDN = dyn_cast_or_null(I)) 0
762 if (!Opened.count(MDN) && !Replacements.count(MDN) && !prune(N, MDN) && 0
763 !isa(MDN)) 0
764 ToVisit.push_back(MDN); 0
765 } ----
766 } 0
767 ----
768 bool llvm::stripNonLineTableDebugInfo(Module &M) { 0
769 bool Changed = false; 0
770 ----
771 // First off, delete the debug intrinsics. ----
772 auto RemoveUses = [&](StringRef Name) { 0
773 if (auto *DbgVal = M.getFunction(Name)) { 0
774 while (!DbgVal->use_empty()) 0
775 cast(DbgVal->user_back())->eraseFromParent(); 0
776 DbgVal->eraseFromParent(); 0
777 Changed = true; 0
778 } ----
779 }; 0
780 RemoveUses("llvm.dbg.declare"); 0
781 RemoveUses("llvm.dbg.label"); 0
782 RemoveUses("llvm.dbg.value"); 0
783 ----
784 // Delete non-CU debug info named metadata nodes. ----
785 for (auto NMI = M.named_metadata_begin(), NME = M.named_metadata_end(); 0
786 NMI != NME;) { 0
787 NamedMDNode *NMD = &*NMI; 0
788 ++NMI; 0
789 // Specifically keep dbg.cu around. ----
790 if (NMD->getName() == "llvm.dbg.cu") 0
791 continue; 0
792 } ----
793 ----
794 // Drop all dbg attachments from global variables. ----
795 for (auto &GV : M.globals()) 0
796 GV.eraseMetadata(LLVMContext::MD_dbg); 0
797 ----
798 DebugTypeInfoRemoval Mapper(M.getContext()); 0
799 auto remap = [&](MDNode *Node) -> MDNode * { 0
800 if (!Node) 0
801 return nullptr; 0
802 Mapper.traverseAndRemap(Node); 0
803 auto *NewNode = Mapper.mapNode(Node); 0
804 Changed |= Node != NewNode; 0
805 Node = NewNode; 0
806 return NewNode; 0
807 }; 0
808 ----
809 // Rewrite the DebugLocs to be equivalent to what ----
810 // -gline-tables-only would have created. ----
811 for (auto &F : M) { 0
812 if (auto *SP = F.getSubprogram()) { 0
813 Mapper.traverseAndRemap(SP); 0
814 auto *NewSP = cast(Mapper.mapNode(SP)); 0
815 Changed |= SP != NewSP; 0
816 F.setSubprogram(NewSP); 0
817 } ----
818 for (auto &BB : F) { 0
819 for (auto &I : BB) { 0
820 auto remapDebugLoc = [&](const DebugLoc &DL) -> DebugLoc { 0
821 auto *Scope = DL.getScope(); 0
822 MDNode *InlinedAt = DL.getInlinedAt(); 0
823 Scope = remap(Scope); 0
824 InlinedAt = remap(InlinedAt); 0
825 return DILocation::get(M.getContext(), DL.getLine(), DL.getCol(), 0
826 Scope, InlinedAt); 0
827 }; 0
828 ----
829 if (I.getDebugLoc() != DebugLoc()) 0
830 I.setDebugLoc(remapDebugLoc(I.getDebugLoc())); 0
831 ----
832 // Remap DILocations in llvm.loop attachments. ----
833 updateLoopMetadataDebugLocations(I, [&](Metadata *MD) -> Metadata * { 0
834 if (auto *Loc = dyn_cast_or_null(MD)) 0
835 return remapDebugLoc(Loc).get(); 0
836 return MD; 0
837 }); ----
838 ----
839 // Strip heapallocsite attachments, they point into the DIType system. ----
840 if (I.hasMetadataOtherThanDebugLoc()) 0
841 I.setMetadata("heapallocsite", nullptr); 0
842 } ----
843 } ----
844 } ----
845 ----
846 // Create a new llvm.dbg.cu, which is equivalent to the one ----
847 // -gline-tables-only would have created. ----
848 for (auto &NMD : M.named_metadata()) { 0
849 SmallVector Ops; 0
850 for (MDNode *Op : NMD.operands()) 0
851 Ops.push_back(remap(Op)); 0
852 ----
853 if (!Changed) 0
854 continue; 0
855 ----
856 NMD.clearOperands(); 0
857 for (auto *Op : Ops) 0
858 if (Op) 0
859 NMD.addOperand(Op); 0
860 } 0
861 return Changed; 0
862 } 0
863 ----
864 unsigned llvm::getDebugMetadataVersionFromModule(const Module &M) { 2 ../DebugInfoTest/example_mips_dbg.ll ../DebugInfoTest/example_mips.ll
865 if (auto *Val = mdconst::dyn_extract_or_null( 4 ../DebugInfoTest/example_mips_dbg.ll ../DebugInfoTest/example_mips.ll
866 M.getModuleFlag("Debug Info Version"))) 2 ../DebugInfoTest/example_mips_dbg.ll ../DebugInfoTest/example_mips.ll
867 return Val->getZExtValue(); 1 ../DebugInfoTest/example_mips_dbg.ll
868 return 0; 1 ../DebugInfoTest/example_mips.ll
869 } ----

871 void Instruction::applyMergedLocation(DILocation *LocA, DILocation *LocB) { 0
872 setDebugLoc(DILocation::getMergedLocation(LocA, LocB)); 0
873 } 0
874 ----
875 void Instruction::mergeDIAssignID( 0
876 ArrayRef SourceInstructions) { ----
877 // Replace all uses (and attachments) of all the DIAssignIDs ----
878 // on SourceInstructions with a single merged value. ----
879 assert(getFunction() && "Uninserted instruction merged"); 0
880 // Collect up the DIAssignID tags. ----
881 SmallVector IDs; 0
882 for (const Instruction *I : SourceInstructions) { 0
883 if (auto *MD = I->getMetadata(LLVMContext::MD_DIAssignID)) 0
884 IDs.push_back(cast(MD)); 0
885 assert(getFunction() == I->getFunction() && 0
886 "Merging with instruction from another function not allowed"); ----
887 } ----
888 ----
889 // Add this instruction's DIAssignID too, if it has one. ----
890 if (auto *MD = getMetadata(LLVMContext::MD_DIAssignID)) 0
891 IDs.push_back(cast(MD)); 0
892 ----
893 if (IDs.empty()) 0
894 return; // No DIAssignID tags to process. 0
895 ----
896 DIAssignID *MergeID = IDs[0]; 0
897 for (auto It = std::next(IDs.begin()), End = IDs.end(); It != End; ++It) { 0
898 if (*It != MergeID) 0
899 at::RAUW(*It, MergeID); 0
900 } ----
901 setMetadata(LLVMContext::MD_DIAssignID, MergeID); 0
902 } 0
903 ----
904 void Instruction::updateLocationAfterHoist() { dropLocation(); } 0
905 ----
906 void Instruction::dropLocation() { 0
907 const DebugLoc &DL = getDebugLoc(); 0
908 if (!DL) 0
909 return; 0
910 ----
911 // If this isn't a call, drop the location to allow a location from a ----
912 // preceding instruction to propagate. ----
913 bool MayLowerToCall = false; 0
914 if (isa(this)) { 0
915 auto *II = dyn_cast(this); 0
916 MayLowerToCall = 0
917 !II || IntrinsicInst::mayLowerToFunctionCall(II->getIntrinsicID()); 0
918 } ----
919 ----
920 if (!MayLowerToCall) { 0
921 setDebugLoc(DebugLoc()); 0
922 return; 0
923 } ----
924 ----
925 // Set a line 0 location for calls to preserve scope information in case ----
926 // inlining occurs. ----
927 DISubprogram *SP = getFunction()->getSubprogram(); 0
928 if (SP) 0
929 // If a function scope is available, set it on the line 0 location. When ----
930 // hoisting a call to a predecessor block, using the function scope avoids ----
931 // making it look like the callee was reached earlier than it should be. ----
932 setDebugLoc(DILocation::get(getContext(), 0, 0, SP)); 0
933 else ----
934 // The parent function has no scope. Go ahead and drop the location. If ----
935 // the parent function is inlined, and the callee has a subprogram, the ----
936 // inliner will attach a location to the call. ----
937 // ----
938 // One alternative is to set a line 0 location with the existing scope and ----
939 // inlinedAt info. The location might be sensitive to when inlining occurs. ----
940 setDebugLoc(DebugLoc()); 0
941 } ----

947 static unsigned map_from_llvmDWARFsourcelanguage(LLVMDWARFSourceLanguage lang) { 0
948 switch (lang) { 0
949 #define HANDLE_DW_LANG(ID, NAME, LOWER_BOUND, VERSION, VENDOR) \ ----
950 case LLVMDWARFSourceLanguage##NAME: \ ----
951 return ID; ----
952 #include "llvm/BinaryFormat/Dwarf.def" ----
953 #undef HANDLE_DW_LANG ----
954 } ----
955 llvm_unreachable("Unhandled Tag"); 0
956 } ----

1705 LLVMMetadataKind LLVMGetMetadataKind(LLVMMetadataRef Metadata) { 0
1706 switch(unwrap(Metadata)->getMetadataID()) { 0
1707 #define HANDLE_METADATA_LEAF(CLASS) \ ----
1708 case Metadata::CLASS##Kind: \ ----
1709 return (LLVMMetadataKind)LLVM##CLASS##MetadataKind; ----
1710 #include "llvm/IR/Metadata.def" ----
1711 default: 0
1712 return (LLVMMetadataKind)LLVMGenericDINodeMetadataKind; 0
1713 } ----
1714 } ----
1715 ----
1716 AssignmentInstRange at::getAssignmentInsts(DIAssignID *ID) { 0
1717 assert(ID && "Expected non-null ID"); 0
1718 LLVMContext &Ctx = ID->getContext(); 0
1719 auto &Map = Ctx.pImpl->AssignmentIDToInstrs; 0
1720 ----
1721 auto MapIt = Map.find(ID); 0
1722 if (MapIt == Map.end()) 0
1723 return make_range(nullptr, nullptr); 0
1724 ----
1725 return make_range(MapIt->second.begin(), MapIt->second.end()); 0
1726 } ----

1735 // one of those already exists first. ----

1737 return make_range(Value::user_iterator(), Value::user_iterator()); 0
1738 ----
1739 return make_range(IDAsValue->user_begin(), IDAsValue->user_end()); 0

1756 OldIDAsValue->replaceAllUsesWith(NewIDAsValue); 0

1782 ----
1783 bool at::calculateFragmentIntersect( 0
1784 const DataLayout &DL, const Value *Dest, uint64_t SliceOffsetInBits, ----
1785 uint64_t SliceSizeInBits, const DbgAssignIntrinsic *DAI, ----
1786 std::optional &Result) { ----
1787 // There are multiple offsets at play in this function, so let's break it ----
1788 // down. Starting with how variables may be stored in allocas: ----
1789 // ----
1790 // 1 Simplest case: variable is alloca sized and starts at offset 0. ----
1791 // 2 Variable is larger than the alloca: the alloca holds just a part of it. ----
1792 // 3 Variable is smaller than the alloca: the alloca may hold multiple ----
1793 // variables. ----
1794 // ----
1795 // Imagine we have a store to the entire alloca. In case (3) the store ----
1796 // affects bits outside of the bounds of each variable. In case (2), where ----
1797 // the alloca holds the Xth bit to the Yth bit of a variable, the ----
1798 // zero-offset store doesn't represent an assignment at offset zero to the ----
1799 // variable. It is an assignment to offset X. ----
1800 // ----
1801 // # Example 1 ----
1802 // Obviously, not all stores are alloca-sized and have zero offset. Imagine ----
1803 // the lower 32 bits of this store are dead and are going to be DSEd: ----
1804 // ----
1805 // store i64 %v, ptr %dest, !DIAssignID !1 ----
1806 // dbg.assign(..., !DIExpression(fragment, 128, 32), !1, %dest, ----
1807 // !DIExpression(DW_OP_plus_uconst, 4)) ----
1808 // ----
1809 // Goal: Given our dead bits at offset:0 size:32 for the store, determine the ----
1810 // part of the variable, which fits in the fragment expressed by the ----
1811 // dbg.assign, that has been killed, if any. ----
1812 // ----
1813 // calculateFragmentIntersect(..., SliceOffsetInBits=0, ----
1814 // SliceSizeInBits=32, Dest=%dest, DAI=dbg.assign) ----
1815 // ----
1816 // Drawing the store (s) in memory followed by the shortened version ($), ----
1817 // then the dbg.assign (d), with the fragment information on a seperate scale ----
1818 // underneath: ----
1819 // ----
1820 // Memory ----
1821 // offset ----
1822 // from ----
1823 // dest 0 63 ----
1824 // | | ----
1825 // s[######] - Original stores 64 bits to Dest. ----
1826 // $----[##] - DSE says the lower 32 bits are dead, to be removed. ----
1827 // d [##] - DAI's address-modifying expression adds 4 bytes to dest. ----
1828 // Variable | | ----
1829 // Fragment 128| ----
1830 // Offsets 159 ----
1831 // ----
1832 // The answer is achieved in a few steps: ----
1833 // 1. Add the fragment offset to the store offset: ----
1834 // SliceOffsetInBits:0 + VarFrag.OffsetInBits:128 = 128 ----
1835 // ----
1836 // 2. Subtract the address-modifying expression offset plus difference ----
1837 // between d.address and dest: ----
1838 // 128 - (expression_offset:32 + (d.address - dest):0) = 96 ----
1839 // ----
1840 // 3. That offset along with the store size (32) represents the bits of the ----
1841 // variable that'd be affected by the store. Call it SliceOfVariable. ----
1842 // Intersect that with DAI's fragment info: ----
1843 // SliceOfVariable DAI_fragment = none ----
1844 // ----
1845 // In this case: none of the dead bits of the store affect DAI. ----
1846 // ----
1847 // # Example 2 ----
1848 // Similar example with the same goal. This time the upper 16 bits ----
1849 // of the store are going to be DSE'd. ----
1850 // ----
1851 // store i64 %v, ptr %dest, !DIAssignID !1 ----
1852 // dbg.assign(..., !DIExpression(fragment, 128, 32), !1, %dest, ----
1853 // !DIExpression(DW_OP_plus_uconst, 4)) ----
1854 // ----
1855 // calculateFragmentIntersect(..., SliceOffsetInBits=48, ----
1856 // SliceSizeInBits=16, Dest=%dest, DAI=dbg.assign) ----
1857 // ----
1858 // Memory ----
1859 // offset ----
1860 // from ----
1861 // dest 0 63 ----
1862 // | | ----
1863 // s[######] - Original stores 64 bits to Dest. ----
1864 // $[####]-- - DSE says the upper 16 bits are dead, to be removed. ----
1865 // d [##] - DAI's address-modifying expression adds 4 bytes to dest. ----
1866 // Variable | | ----
1867 // Fragment 128| ----
1868 // Offsets 159 ----
1869 // ----
1870 // Using the same steps in the first example: ----
1871 // 1. SliceOffsetInBits:48 + VarFrag.OffsetInBits:128 = 176 ----
1872 // 2. 176 - (expression_offset:32 + (d.address - dest):0) = 144 ----
1873 // 3. SliceOfVariable offset = 144, size = 16: ----
1874 // SliceOfVariable DAI_fragment = (offset: 144, size: 16) ----
1875 // SliceOfVariable tells us the bits of the variable described by DAI that are ----
1876 // affected by the DSE. ----
1877 if (DAI->isKillAddress()) 0
1878 return false; 0
1879 ----
1880 DIExpression::FragmentInfo VarFrag = DAI->getFragmentOrEntireVariable(); 0
1881 if (VarFrag.SizeInBits == 0) 0
1882 return false; // Variable size is unknown. 0
1883 ----
1884 // Calculate the difference between Dest and the dbg.assign address + ----
1885 // address-modifying expression. ----
1886 int64_t PointerOffsetInBits; ----
1887 { ----
1888 auto DestOffsetInBytes = DAI->getAddress()->getPointerOffsetFrom(Dest, DL); 0
1889 if (!DestOffsetInBytes) 0
1890 return false; // Can't calculate difference in addresses. 0
1891 ----
1892 int64_t ExprOffsetInBytes; ----
1893 if (!DAI->getAddressExpression()->extractIfOffset(ExprOffsetInBytes)) 0
1894 return false; 0
1895 ----
1896 int64_t PointerOffsetInBytes = *DestOffsetInBytes + ExprOffsetInBytes; 0
1897 PointerOffsetInBits = PointerOffsetInBytes * 8; 0
1898 } ----
1899 ----
1900 // Adjust the slice offset so that we go from describing the a slice ----
1901 // of memory to a slice of the variable. ----
1902 int64_t NewOffsetInBits = 0
1903 SliceOffsetInBits + VarFrag.OffsetInBits - PointerOffsetInBits; 0
1904 if (NewOffsetInBits < 0) 0
1905 return false; // Fragment offsets can only be positive. 0
1906 DIExpression::FragmentInfo SliceOfVariable(SliceSizeInBits, NewOffsetInBits); 0
1907 // Intersect the variable slice with DAI's fragment to trim it down to size. ----
1908 DIExpression::FragmentInfo TrimmedSliceOfVariable = ----
1909 DIExpression::FragmentInfo::intersect(SliceOfVariable, VarFrag); 0
1910 if (TrimmedSliceOfVariable == VarFrag) 0
1911 Result = std::nullopt; 0
1912 else ----
1913 Result = TrimmedSliceOfVariable; 0
1914 return true; 0
1915 } ----
1916 ----
1917 /// Collect constant properies (base, size, offset) of \p StoreDest. ----
1918 /// Return std::nullopt if any properties are not constants or the ----
1919 /// offset from the base pointer is negative. ----
1920 static std::optional ----
1921 getAssignmentInfoImpl(const DataLayout &DL, const Value *StoreDest, 0
1922 TypeSize SizeInBits) { ----
1923 if (SizeInBits.isScalable()) 0
1924 return std::nullopt; 0
1925 APInt GEPOffset(DL.getIndexTypeSizeInBits(StoreDest->getType()), 0); 0
1926 const Value *Base = StoreDest->stripAndAccumulateConstantOffsets( 0
1927 DL, GEPOffset, /*AllowNonInbounds*/ true); ----
1928 ----
1929 if (GEPOffset.isNegative()) 0
1930 return std::nullopt; 0
1931 ----
1932 uint64_t OffsetInBytes = GEPOffset.getLimitedValue(); 0
1933 // Check for overflow. ----
1934 if (OffsetInBytes == UINT64_MAX) 0
1935 return std::nullopt; 0
1936 if (const auto *Alloca = dyn_cast(Base)) 0
1937 return AssignmentInfo(DL, Alloca, OffsetInBytes * 8, SizeInBits); 0
1938 return std::nullopt; 0
1939 } 0

1941 std::optional at::getAssignmentInfo(const DataLayout &DL, 0
1942 const MemIntrinsic *I) { ----
1943 const Value *StoreDest = I->getRawDest(); 0
1944 // Assume 8 bit bytes. ----
1945 auto *ConstLengthInBytes = dyn_cast(I->getLength()); 0
1946 if (!ConstLengthInBytes) 0
1947 // We can't use a non-const size, bail. ----
1948 return std::nullopt; 0
1949 uint64_t SizeInBits = 8 * ConstLengthInBytes->getZExtValue(); 0
1950 return getAssignmentInfoImpl(DL, StoreDest, TypeSize::getFixed(SizeInBits)); 0
1951 } ----

1965 /// Returns nullptr if the assignment shouldn't be attributed to this variable. ----
1966 static CallInst *emitDbgAssign(AssignmentInfo Info, Value *Val, Value *Dest, 0
1967 Instruction &StoreLikeInst, ----
1968 const VarRecord &VarRec, DIBuilder &DIB) { ----
1969 auto *ID = StoreLikeInst.getMetadata(LLVMContext::MD_DIAssignID); 0
1970 assert(ID && "Store instruction must have DIAssignID metadata"); 0
1971 (void)ID; ----
1972 ----
1973 const uint64_t StoreStartBit = Info.OffsetInBits; 0
1974 const uint64_t StoreEndBit = Info.OffsetInBits + Info.SizeInBits; 0
1975 ----
1976 uint64_t FragStartBit = StoreStartBit; 0
1977 uint64_t FragEndBit = StoreEndBit; 0
1978 ----
1979 bool StoreToWholeVariable = Info.StoreToWholeAlloca; 0
1980 if (auto Size = VarRec.Var->getSizeInBits()) { 0
1981 // NOTE: trackAssignments doesn't understand base expressions yet, so all ----
1982 // variables that reach here are guaranteed to start at offset 0 in the ----
1983 // alloca. ----
1984 const uint64_t VarStartBit = 0; 0
1985 const uint64_t VarEndBit = *Size; 0
1986 ----
1987 // FIXME: trim FragStartBit when nonzero VarStartBit is supported. ----
1988 FragEndBit = std::min(FragEndBit, VarEndBit); 0
1989 ----
1990 // Discard stores to bits outside this variable. ----
1991 if (FragStartBit >= FragEndBit) 0
1992 return nullptr; 0
1993 ----
1994 StoreToWholeVariable = FragStartBit <= VarStartBit && FragEndBit >= *Size; 0
1995 } ----
1996 ----
1997 DIExpression *Expr = ----
1998 DIExpression::get(StoreLikeInst.getContext(), std::nullopt); 0
1999 if (!StoreToWholeVariable) { 0
2000 auto R = DIExpression::createFragmentExpression(Expr, FragStartBit, 0
2001 FragEndBit - FragStartBit); ----
2002 assert(R.has_value() && "failed to create fragment expression"); 0
2003 Expr = *R; 0
2004 } ----
2005 DIExpression *AddrExpr = ----
2006 DIExpression::get(StoreLikeInst.getContext(), std::nullopt); 0
2007 return DIB.insertDbgAssign(&StoreLikeInst, Val, VarRec.Var, Expr, Dest, 0
2008 AddrExpr, VarRec.DL); 0
2009 } ----

2013 ----
2014 void at::trackAssignments(Function::iterator Start, Function::iterator End, 0
2015 const StorageToVarsMap &Vars, const DataLayout &DL, ----
2016 bool DebugPrints) { ----
2017 // Early-exit if there are no interesting variables. ----
2018 if (Vars.empty()) 0
2019 return; 0
2020 ----
2021 auto &Ctx = Start->getContext(); 0
2022 auto &Module = *Start->getModule(); 0
2023 ----
2024 // Undef type doesn't matter, so long as it isn't void. Let's just use i1. ----
2025 auto *Undef = UndefValue::get(Type::getInt1Ty(Ctx)); 0
2026 DIBuilder DIB(Module, /*AllowUnresolved*/ false); 0
2027 ----
2028 // Scan the instructions looking for stores to local variables' storage. ----
2029 LLVM_DEBUG(errs() << "# Scanning instructions\n"); 0
2030 for (auto BBI = Start; BBI != End; ++BBI) { 0
2031 for (Instruction &I : *BBI) { 0
2032 ----
2033 std::optional Info; 0
2034 Value *ValueComponent = nullptr; 0
2035 Value *DestComponent = nullptr; 0
2036 if (auto *AI = dyn_cast(&I)) { 0
2037 // We want to track the variable's stack home from its alloca's ----
2038 // position onwards so we treat it as an assignment (where the stored ----
2039 // value is Undef). ----
2040 Info = getAssignmentInfo(DL, AI); 0
2041 ValueComponent = Undef; 0
2042 DestComponent = AI; 0
2043 } else if (auto *SI = dyn_cast(&I)) { 0
2044 Info = getAssignmentInfo(DL, SI); 0
2045 ValueComponent = SI->getValueOperand(); 0
2046 DestComponent = SI->getPointerOperand(); 0
2047 } else if (auto *MI = dyn_cast(&I)) { 0
2048 Info = getAssignmentInfo(DL, MI); 0
2049 // May not be able to represent this value easily. ----
2050 ValueComponent = Undef; 0
2051 DestComponent = MI->getOperand(0); 0
2052 } else if (auto *MI = dyn_cast(&I)) { 0
2053 Info = getAssignmentInfo(DL, MI); 0
2054 // If we're zero-initing we can state the assigned value is zero, ----
2055 // otherwise use undef. ----
2056 auto *ConstValue = dyn_cast(MI->getOperand(1)); 0
2057 if (ConstValue && ConstValue->isZero()) 0
2058 ValueComponent = ConstValue; 0
2059 else ----
2060 ValueComponent = Undef; 0
2061 DestComponent = MI->getOperand(0); 0
2062 } else { ----
2063 // Not a store-like instruction. ----
2064 continue; 0
2065 } ----
2066 ----
2067 assert(ValueComponent && DestComponent); 0
2068 LLVM_DEBUG(errs() << "SCAN: Found store-like: " << I << "\n"); 0
2069 ----
2070 // Check if getAssignmentInfo failed to understand this store. ----
2071 if (!Info.has_value()) { 0
2072 LLVM_DEBUG( 0
2073 errs() ----
2074 << " | SKIP: Untrackable store (e.g. through non-const gep)\n"); ----
2075 continue; 0
2076 } ----
2077 LLVM_DEBUG(errs() << " | BASE: " << *Info->Base << "\n"); 0
2078 ----
2079 // Check if the store destination is a local variable with debug info. ----
2080 auto LocalIt = Vars.find(Info->Base); 0
2081 if (LocalIt == Vars.end()) { 0
2082 LLVM_DEBUG( 0
2083 errs() ----
2084 << " | SKIP: Base address not associated with local variable\n"); ----
2085 continue; 0
2086 } ----
2087 ----
2088 DIAssignID *ID = ----
2089 cast_or_null(I.getMetadata(LLVMContext::MD_DIAssignID)); 0
2090 if (!ID) { 0
2091 ID = DIAssignID::getDistinct(Ctx); 0
2092 I.setMetadata(LLVMContext::MD_DIAssignID, ID); 0
2093 } ----
2094 ----
2095 for (const VarRecord &R : LocalIt->second) { 0
2096 auto *Assign = ----
2097 emitDbgAssign(*Info, ValueComponent, DestComponent, I, R, DIB); 0
2098 (void)Assign; ----
2099 LLVM_DEBUG(if (Assign) errs() << " > INSERT: " << *Assign << "\n"); 0
2100 } 0
2101 } ----
2102 } ----
2103 } 0
2104 ----
2105 bool AssignmentTrackingPass::runOnFunction(Function &F) { 0
2106 // No value in assignment tracking without optimisations. ----
2107 if (F.hasFnAttribute(Attribute::OptimizeNone)) 0
2108 return /*Changed*/ false; 0
2109 ----
2110 bool Changed = false; 0
2111 auto *DL = &F.getParent()->getDataLayout(); 0
2112 // Collect a map of {backing storage : dbg.declares} (currently "backing ----
2113 // storage" is limited to Allocas). We'll use this to find dbg.declares to ----
2114 // delete after running `trackAssignments`. ----
2115 DenseMap> DbgDeclares; 0
2116 // Create another similar map of {storage : variables} that we'll pass to ----
2117 // trackAssignments. ----
2118 StorageToVarsMap Vars; 0
2119 for (auto &BB : F) { 0
2120 for (auto &I : BB) { 0
2121 DbgDeclareInst *DDI = dyn_cast(&I); 0
2122 if (!DDI) 0
2123 continue; 0
2124 // FIXME: trackAssignments doesn't let you specify any modifiers to the ----
2125 // variable (e.g. fragment) or location (e.g. offset), so we have to ----
2126 // leave dbg.declares with non-empty expressions in place. ----
2127 if (DDI->getExpression()->getNumElements() != 0) 0
2128 continue; 0
2129 if (!DDI->getAddress()) 0
2130 continue; 0
2131 if (AllocaInst *Alloca = 0
2132 dyn_cast(DDI->getAddress()->stripPointerCasts())) { 0
2133 // FIXME: Skip VLAs for now (let these variables use dbg.declares). ----
2134 if (!Alloca->isStaticAlloca()) 0
2135 continue; 0
2136 // Similarly, skip scalable vectors (use dbg.declares instead). ----
2137 if (auto Sz = Alloca->getAllocationSize(*DL); Sz && Sz->isScalable()) 0
2138 continue; 0
2139 DbgDeclares[Alloca].insert(DDI); 0
2140 Vars[Alloca].insert(VarRecord(DDI)); 0
2141 } ----
2142 } ----
2143 } ----
2144 ----
2145 // FIXME: Locals can be backed by caller allocas (sret, byval). ----
2146 // Note: trackAssignments doesn't respect dbg.declare's IR positions (as it ----
2147 // doesn't "understand" dbg.declares). However, this doesn't appear to break ----
2148 // any rules given this description of dbg.declare from ----
2149 // llvm/docs/SourceLevelDebugging.rst: ----
2150 // ----
2151 // It is not control-dependent, meaning that if a call to llvm.dbg.declare ----
2152 // exists and has a valid location argument, that address is considered to ----
2153 // be the true home of the variable across its entire lifetime. ----
2154 trackAssignments(F.begin(), F.end(), Vars, *DL); 0
2155 ----
2156 // Delete dbg.declares for variables now tracked with assignment tracking. ----
2157 for (auto &P : DbgDeclares) { 0
2158 const AllocaInst *Alloca = P.first; 0
2159 auto Markers = at::getAssignmentMarkers(Alloca); 0
2160 (void)Markers; ----
2161 for (DbgDeclareInst *DDI : P.second) { 0
2162 // Assert that the alloca that DDI uses is now linked to a dbg.assign ----
2163 // describing the same variable (i.e. check that this dbg.declare has ----
2164 // been replaced by a dbg.assign). Use DebugVariableAggregate to Discard ----
2165 // the fragment part because trackAssignments may alter the ----
2166 // fragment. e.g. if the alloca is smaller than the variable, then ----
2167 // trackAssignments will create an alloca-sized fragment for the ----
2168 // dbg.assign. ----
2169 assert(llvm::any_of(Markers, [DDI](DbgAssignIntrinsic *DAI) { 0
2170 return DebugVariableAggregate(DAI) == DebugVariableAggregate(DDI); ----
2171 })); ----
2172 // Delete DDI because the variable location is now tracked using ----
2173 // assignment tracking. ----
2174 DDI->eraseFromParent(); 0
2175 Changed = true; 0
2176 } ----
2177 } ----
2178 return Changed; 0
2179 } 0

2199 PreservedAnalyses AssignmentTrackingPass::run(Function &F, 0
2200 FunctionAnalysisManager &AM) { ----
2201 if (!runOnFunction(F)) 0
2202 return PreservedAnalyses::all(); 0
2203 ----
2204 // Record that this module uses assignment tracking. It doesn't matter that ----
2205 // some functons in the module may not use it - the debug info in those ----
2206 // functions will still be handled properly. ----
2207 setAssignmentTrackingModuleFlag(*F.getParent()); 0
2208 ----
2209 // Q: Can we return a less conservative set than just CFGAnalyses? Can we ----
2210 // return PreservedAnalyses::all()? ----
2211 PreservedAnalyses PA; 0
2212 PA.preserveSet(); 0
2213 return PA; 0
2214 } 0
2215 ----
2216 PreservedAnalyses AssignmentTrackingPass::run(Module &M, 0
2217 ModuleAnalysisManager &AM) { ----
2218 bool Changed = false; 0
2219 for (auto &F : M) 0
2220 Changed |= runOnFunction(F); 0
2221 ----
2222 if (!Changed) 0
2223 return PreservedAnalyses::all(); 0
2224 ----
2225 // Record that this module uses assignment tracking. ----
2226 setAssignmentTrackingModuleFlag(M); 0
2227 ----
2228 // Q: Can we return a less conservative set than just CFGAnalyses? Can we ----
2229 // return PreservedAnalyses::all()? ----
2230 PreservedAnalyses PA; 0
2231 PA.preserveSet(); 0
2232 return PA; 0
2233 } 0
